# No em dashes

Never use em dashes (—) in chat responses, commit messages, PR descriptions, documentation, comments, or UI copy.

## Use instead

- Commas for light asides
- Parentheses for supplementary detail
- Colons to introduce explanations
- Separate sentences when clarity needs a break

## Examples

Bad: "The booking failed — the API returned 404."
Good: "The booking failed because the API returned 404."

Bad: "Nest — our AI assistant — confirmed the slot."
Good: "Nest, our AI assistant, confirmed the slot."
